Quantitative Ratings (Likert scale, 1-5):
Understanding:
How well did you understand the main points of the user analysis report? (1 = Not at all, 5 = Very well)
How clear was the description of the user's typical behavior and emotional expressions? (1 = Not at all clear, 5 = Very clear)
Plausibility:
Based on the report, how plausible do you find the analysis of the user's emotional states? (1 = Not at all plausible, 5 = Very plausible)
Do you think the described emotions and behaviors are consistent with what you might expect from someone in this online context? (1 = Not at all, 5 = Very much so)
Usefulness (Content Moderation Context):
How helpful would this report be in deciding on an appropriate moderation action for this user (e.g., warning, temporary ban, no action)? (1 = Not at all helpful, 5 = Very helpful)
Does this report provide you with enough information to understand the user's potential impact on the online community? (1 = Not at all, 5 = Very much so)


Qualitative Feedback (after each report and/or at the end of the study):
Open-ended questions:
What aspects of the report were most helpful in understanding the user?
What aspects of the report were unclear or confusing?
How could the report be improved to be more informative or useful?
How confident are you in your assessment of the user based on this report? Why?
Do you have any concerns or limitations you see when using automated systems for such tasks?
If the report had included information about [specific element, e.g., "reason for assessment, data sources, and methods"], would that have been helpful? Why or why not?


